What's a Codeshare?
Simply put, it means an airline can sell tickets for a flight that’s run by another airline. This means their loyal customers can still book through them to earn miles. Sometimes the booking airline and operating airline each apply different bag/seating fees or other rules. You can check details directly with the airlines themselves.

What's a Codeshare?
Simply put, it means an airline can sell tickets for a flight that’s run by another airline. This means their loyal customers can still book through them to earn miles. Sometimes the booking airline and operating airline each apply different bag/seating fees or other rules. You can check details directly with the airlines themselves.

What's a Codeshare?
Simply put, it means an airline can sell tickets for a flight that’s run by another airline. This means their loyal customers can still book through them to earn miles. Sometimes the booking airline and operating airline each apply different bag/seating fees or other rules. You can check details directly with the airlines themselves.

We’re not the seller.
At KAYAK we don’t set the prices, so it’s not possible for us to guarantee what other companies are selling.

Why aren’t prices accurate 100% of the time?
Prices on airline seats, hotel rooms and car rentals can change frequently. Several people may also be trying to buy the same travel option simultaneously. As a result, you may find, on occasion, that certain prices are no longer available.

Flexible options by airline

Airlines are offering enhanced flexibility to travelers due to COVID-19. Find a summary of various airline policies below. Confirm terms and policies on each airline’s site.

More information about COVID-19 and travel.

Alaska Airlines

Alaska Saver fares booked before April 30 are cancellable without a fee. Alaska Main and First fares booked before April 30 are eligible for a one-time change or cancellation without a fee. For all canceled fares, a travel credit will be issued.

American Airlines

American flights booked before May 31 are eligible for a one-time change or cancellation without a fee. For all canceled fares, a travel credit will be issued. For travel originally booked through September 30, credit will be valid through December 31, 2021. All other credit will be valid for one year.

Delta

Delta flights booked before May 31 are eligible for a one-time change or cancellation without a fee (travel credit issued for future flights made within one year).

Frontier

Frontier flights booked before April 15 are eligible for a one-time change or cancellation without a fee (travel credit issued for future flights booked within 90 days). If you change your ticket, new travel must be completed by November 9.

Hawaiian Airlines

Hawaiian flights booked through May are eligible for a one-time change without a fee.

JetBlue

JetBlue flights booked before April 30 for travel through January 4 are eligible for a one-time change or cancellation without a fee (travel credit issued for future flights made within one year).

Southwest

Southwest flights are always eligible for change or cancellation without a fee.

United Airlines

United flights booked before April 30 are eligible for a one-time change or cancellation without a fee (travel credit issued for future flights made within one year).
